-- Red Sox, Dodgers Agree to Nine-Player Trade, MLB.com Reports
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-25T19:53:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-25/red-sox-dodgers-agree-to-nine-player-trade-mlb-com-reports.html
The Boston Red Sox and Los Angeles
Dodgers have agreed to a nine-player trade, Major League
Baseball’s website reported.  Boston sends first baseman  Adrian Gonzalez , pitcher Josh
Beckett, outfielder  Carl Crawford  and infielder Nick Punto to
Los Angeles, while receiving first baseman James Loney and four
prospects: pitchers Rubby De La Rosa and Allen Webster,
infielder Ivan De Jesus and outfielder Jerry Sands, MLB.com
said.  The deal is pending approval from baseball officials,
MLB.com said. Gonzazlez today posted on his Twitter account that
he’s joining the Dodgers.  “Excited to get back to Cali and be a part of
Dodgertown,” he wrote on Twitter.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
